1
00:00:05,360 --> 00:00:07,860
Something comes to mind 
from my own experience,

2
00:00:08,020 --> 00:00:10,420
when we talk about family.

3
00:00:10,550 --> 00:00:13,569
I grew up happily 
in a particular family,

4
00:00:13,569 --> 00:00:17,318
but around time 
I turned thirteen,

5
00:00:17,918 --> 00:00:22,696
[I] became … And maybe, 
this is common—

6
00:00:22,696 --> 00:00:24,874
the onset of puberty,
etc.

7
00:00:24,874 --> 00:00:27,634
To start questioning 
and examining everything.

8
00:00:27,704 --> 00:00:31,337
[Who am I?]

9
00:00:31,337 --> 00:00:34,819
But one day, in the kitchen …

10
00:00:34,819 --> 00:00:37,751
My mother is there, talking to me, 
like, washing and talking.

11
00:00:37,751 --> 00:00:39,813
I’m sitting at the table, 
eating something.

12
00:00:39,813 --> 00:00:42,630
And suddenly it occurred to me,
and I said,

13
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:49,977
“This lady is speaking like 
she totally knows me.

14
00:00:49,977 --> 00:00:53,226
Like I’m very known to her.

15
00:00:53,396 --> 00:00:59,079
And I am assuming that 
I know her very well.

16
00:00:59,079 --> 00:01:02,112
And she is intimately 
known to me.”

17
00:01:02,202 --> 00:01:09,810
But then I thought, “I don’t think 
I’ve clearly focused

18
00:01:09,810 --> 00:01:14,598
on my mother’s face
for a very long time”,

19
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:18,000
’cause your mother’s just always 
part of the environment.

20
00:01:18,677 --> 00:01:23,191
So since these strange feelings 
came to me,

21
00:01:23,341 --> 00:01:25,445
I waited, when she came …

22
00:01:25,445 --> 00:01:28,819
She’s just going on, talking 
about this, that, the other things …

23
00:01:28,819 --> 00:01:30,873
But then when she came
and looked at me …

24
00:01:30,873 --> 00:01:35,262
I looked at, I started 
scrutinizing her face,

25
00:01:35,262 --> 00:01:41,411
and for a few moments 
I couldn’t recognize, who she was.

26
00:01:41,411 --> 00:01:47,751
And I thought, “This is totally 
bizarre circumstance.”

27
00:01:49,706 --> 00:01:54,070
Then I started looking at myself 
in the mirror,

28
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:58,304
and I couldn’t recognize, 
who I was.

29
00:01:59,874 --> 00:02:05,920
And I thought, “This is extra-bizarre.
Trés bizarre!”

30
00:02:07,281 --> 00:02:11,494
A psychoanalyst will say, 
“Yes, with the onset of puberty,

31
00:02:11,494 --> 00:02:17,437
if the adolescent youth 
becomes very …”, whatever.

32
00:02:17,437 --> 00:02:21,125
Like, when my brother, 
the urologist, was in med school,

33
00:02:21,125 --> 00:02:24,783
he had this girlfriend …

34
00:02:27,293 --> 00:02:32,395
And, who I was, sort of, 
if you want to say,

35
00:02:32,395 --> 00:02:35,713
preaching to, but talking to 
about philosophical things.

36
00:02:35,713 --> 00:02:43,391
And she was confiding in me 
that she was asking herself,

37
00:02:43,391 --> 00:02:45,747
“Who am I? 
Where’ve I come from?”,
 

38
00:02:45,747 --> 00:02:51,921
this type of
identity questions.

39
00:02:51,921 --> 00:02:54,450
What comes under the heading 
of self-determination

40
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:56,289
in Hegelian language.

41
00:02:56,489 --> 00:03:00,280
So I thought she was 
really cool person.

42
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:03,033
Because I thought, 
“Oh, this is somebody I can relate to.

43
00:03:03,033 --> 00:03:06,836
She has self-doubts.”

44
00:03:06,836 --> 00:03:10,436
And when I brought it up 
to my brother,

45
00:03:10,436 --> 00:03:14,059
he said, “Oh, she is just going
through a phase.

46
00:03:14,059 --> 00:03:16,322
She’ll get over that.”

47
00:03:16,442 --> 00:03:20,461
And I thought, 
“Means she’s going to get over

48
00:03:20,461 --> 00:03:25,640
inquiring who she is, 
trying to understand, who she is,

49
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:29,609
where she’s come from, 
what her purpose is …”

50
00:03:29,609 --> 00:03:33,671
I was shocked.
I thought,

51
00:03:33,671 --> 00:03:35,763
“No, she shouldn’t 
get over that.”

52
00:03:35,763 --> 00:03:41,166
Human form of life 
is very rarely achieved.

53
00:03:41,216 --> 00:03:46,241
Like other life forms, 
it’s temporary.

54
00:03:46,241 --> 00:03:48,846
All the different life forms 
are temporary.

55
00:03:48,846 --> 00:03:52,634
But in this one there’s …

56
00:03:52,634 --> 00:03:56,833
fortunate souls may get 
that chance of association

57
00:03:56,833 --> 00:04:01,892
with a sadguru—
guru and Vaishnav,

58
00:04:01,894 --> 00:04:03,574
and engage in Kṛṣṇa culture.

